A former bank teller and a trader were on Tuesday charged with stealing over Sh2.8 million from bank accounts belonging to a dead man. 

The suspects, Eutycus Muguna Mutembei and Ayugu Eugene Shivachi, denied 13 counts before Milimani Chief Magistrate Martha Mutuku. 

State Prosecutor Anderson Gikunda said the two cybercrime suspects used a computer to access the bank accounts of the late Amos Ngatia Muiruri, who died in November 2020. 



