Mr Gikunda said the suspects accessed irregularly Muiruri’s accounts at KCB Bank, Equity Bank and NCBA Bank. 

The alleged offences were committed late last year. 

The two are charged alongside a taxi driver and his wife for preparing to commit a felony. 

Police said the four suspects were arrested in Makuyu, Murang’a and 47 Safaricom sim cards registered under different names were recovered. 



